    "on bioscientific university students and especially evaluating eHealth literacy (digital literacy in health), they concluded that university education programs applied to develop digital and scientific skills in health education should be improved to meet future needs [5].",
    "Digital health was incorporated as an elective subject in an integrated medical degree program for a study in Hamburg, Germany.",
    "Consequently, in a poll evaluating the courses presented in the given semester, this class received the highest overall satisfaction, reflecting students' general fulfillment with digital health education [6].",
    "In another study in Germany, distinct modules with learning objectives were created for each academic year of medical school to teach digital competencies, focusing on digital challenges related to the relevant medical application fields.",
    "Given the rapid digitalization of medicine, they underlined the importance of teaching digital literacy in undergraduate medical education [7].In general, 21st-century students are compelled to be proficient digital natives."
